    "body": "hmm, how would this work?\r\n\r\nWhat if we did `@log` instead? Add if method arg names match event arg names, it uses them, or you could provide kwargs to override values like so:\r\n\r\n```vyper\r\nevent Transfer:\r\n    sender: indexed(address)\r\n    receiver: indexed(address)\r\n    amount: uint256\r\n\r\nevent Approval:\r\n    owner: indexed(address)\r\n    spender: indexed(address)\r\n    amount: uint256\r\n\r\ntotalSupply: public(uint256)\r\nbalanceOf: public(HashMap[address, uint256])\r\nallowance: public(HashMap[address, HashMap[address, uint256]])\r\n...\r\n\r\n\r\n@external\r\n@log(Transfer, sender=msg.sender)\r\ndef transfer(receiver: address, amount: uint256) -> bool:\r\n    self.balanceOf[msg.sender] -= amount\r\n    self.balanceOf[receiver] += amount\r\n    return True\r\n\r\n\r\n@external\r\n@log(Approval, owner=msg.sender)\r\ndef approve(spender: address, amount: uint256) -> bool:\r\n    self.allowance[msg.sender][spender] = amount\r\n    return True\r\n\r\n\r\n@external\r\n@log(Transfer)\r\ndef transferFrom(sender: address, receiver: address, amount: uint256) -> bool:\r\n    self.allowance[sender][msg.sender] -= amount\r\n    self.balanceOf[sender] -= amount\r\n    self.balanceOf[receiver] += amount\r\n    return True\r\n\r\n\r\n@external\r\n@log(Transfer, sender=ZERO_ADDRESS)\r\ndef mint(receiver: address, amount: uint256) -> bool:\r\n    assert self.isMinter[msg.sender]\r\n    self.totalSupply += amount\r\n    self.balanceOf[receiver] += amount\r\n    return True\r\n\r\n\r\n@external\r\n@log(Transfer, sender=msg.sender, receiver=ZERO_ADDRESS)\r\ndef burn(amount: uint256) -> bool:\r\n    self.totalSupply -= amount\r\n    self.balanceOf[msg.sender] -= amount\r\n    return True\r\n```\r\n\r\n",
