    "body": "Another idea: if you don't provide an event definition type, it will create it's own\r\n\r\n```vyper\r\n@external\r\n@log(old_owner=msg.sender, indexed=True)\r\n# Creates `UpdateOwner(old_owner: indexed(address), new_owner: indexed(address))`\r\ndef updateOwner(new_owner: address):\r\n    assert self.owner == msg.sender\r\n    self.owner = new_owner\r\n```\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nedit: I think this is what you originally meant to do, but I think with the kwargs syntax it works nicer",
